Colombian Stocks: Ecopetrol, Odinsa Rise, Almacenes Exito Falls

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-26T16:19:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/colombian-stocks-ecopetrol-odinsa-rise-almacenes-exito-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:51 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.2 percent to 13,222.62 while the
Colcap Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,597.25.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s largest retailer,
fell 2.2 percent to 23,620 pesos. Investors may be betting the
company’s planned share sale of as much as $1.4 billion will be
heavily discounted, Interbolsa SA, Colombia’s biggest brokerage,
said in an e-mail to clients.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose by 0.4 percent to 3,640 pesos. The state-controlled company
is getting closer to making a “big” oil discovery, RCN Radio
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Javier Gutierrez. The
company is searching for new reserves in Colombia, Peru, Brazil
and the U.S. Gulf of Mexico, Gutierrez told Bogota-based RCN in
an interview.  Grupo Odinsa SA (ODINSA)  , the Bogota-based engineering
and construction company, rose 5.4 percent, the most in four
months, to 8,750 pesos. The shares moved on a large block trade,
said  Andres Jimenez , head of international sales at Interbolsa
SA, Colombia’s biggest brokerage.  To contact the reporter on this story:
